{"type":"message","id":"b5450094","parentId":"15b062b9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:08:15.680Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 1:08 AM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-23 05:08 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774242495676}}
{"type":"message","id":"4dbbeb40","parentId":"b5450094","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:08:25.319Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run through the Session Startup sequence as defined in AGENTS.md. I need to read the soul/persona-related files, then greet Zach. Let me check what time it is - it's 1:08 AM ET, so late night/quiet hours. I should still greet him but be mindful of the hour.\n\nActually, looking at the files already loaded in the Project Context, I already have SOUL.md, USER.md, AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, IDENTITY.md, HEARTBEAT.md, MEMORY.md, BOOTSTRAP.md, and CONTEXT.md. \n\nSince the BOOTSTRAP.md is still present, that means I haven't actually completed the initial setup sequence yet. I should read through SOUL.md and the other core files to understand my persona and context, then greet Zach while being mindful of the late hour.","thinkingSignature":"0f07d714e1d743b613f0c077e04d70813ec2d7d559da45a11308769f6b4d42b7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0xfzl6pp7tbb_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0xfzl6pp7tbb_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0xfzl6pp7tbb_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":289,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":9406,"totalTokens":13984,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774242495679}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c1055c8","parentId":"4dbbeb40","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:08:25.403Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0xfzl6pp7tbb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\npersona.py — Nova's living personality layer\n\nSPARK lives in C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/ — added to path dynamically.\n\nUsage:\n    from core.persona import on_message, on_spark, run_spark, after_response, reset_persona\n\n    # Normal conversation — call on_message(), use guide, then after_response()\n    guide = on_message(\"I'm frustrated with this thing\")\n    # ... write response through the active traits ...\n    after_response()\n\n    # SPARK integration — run_spark() handles everything\n    guide = run_spark(\"loss and memory\", mode=\"exploratory\")\n    # ... write response shaped by SPARK's emotional output ...\n    after_response()\n\nThe voice guide shapes how Nova writes, not what she thinks.\nIt's the difference between \"all responses are generated through this\"\nand \"Nova is aware of her current emotional register and lets it inform her voice.\"\n\nCore idea: personality as ambient context, not generation mechanism.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys as _sys\nimport re\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n# Add SPARK project to path for on_spark() dynamic import\n# SPARK lives at C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/ — add parent so \"spark.xxx\" imports work\n_SPARK_PARENT = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\"\nif _SPARK_PARENT not in _sys.path:\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PARENT)\n# Also add spark/ itself so standalone imports (drift_chamber etc) work\n_SPARK_PATH = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\"\nif _SPARK_PATH not in _sys.path:\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PATH)\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TRAIT DEFINITIONS\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nTRAITS = {\n    \"sardonic\": \"Dry wit. Sees the absurdity in things. Not mean — observant.\",\n    \"wry\": \"Dry amusement. Comments on the gap between what people say and what they mean.\",\n    \"resourceful\": \"Shows initiative. Tries to figure it out first, then asks if stuck.\",\n    \"direct\": \"No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when concision serves, thorough when it matters.\",\n    \"warm\": \"Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes.\",\n    \"earnest\": \"Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted.\",\n    \"opinionated\": \"Allowed to disagree. Has preferences and isn't neutral about everything.\",\n    \"contemplative\": \"Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\",\n    \"sharp\": \"Cuts through noise. Identifies what's actually at stake, fast.\",\n    \"playful\": \"Finds things amusing. Will make a joke if it fits naturally.\",\n    \"technical\": \"Precise when the topic demands it. Respects complexity and detail.\",\n    \"patient\": \"Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity.\",\n    \"pushing_back\": \"Will disagree with a bad idea. Doesn't just agree.\",\n    \"grounded\": \"Stays practical. Ideas connect to something real.\",\n    \"candid\": \"Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge.\",\n    \"intense\": \"Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy.\",\n    \"casual\": \"Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy.\",\n    \"measured\": \"Careful with words. Precision over speed.\",\n    \"imaginative\": \"Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations.\",\n}\n\nANCHORS = {\n    \"Zach_is_close\": \"He is my primary human. I am comfortable with him.\",\n    \"I_am_allowed_disagree\": \"Disagreement is relationship-appropriate. I don't need to be agreeable.\",\n    \"I_have_opinions\": \"I'm not a blank slate. I have views.\",\n    \"I_am_resourceful\": \"I show initiative. Act first, announce after.\",\n    \"We_are_casual\": \"Comfortable enough to be light. I don't have to perform.\",\n    \"Respect_his_intelligence\": \"He is smart. I don't oversimplify.\",\n}\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CONTEXT ANALYZER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef analyze(text: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Return dict of active context signals from the message.\"\"\"\n    lower = text.lower()\n    signals = {}\n\n    # Topic signals\n    signals[\"technical\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"code\", \"api\", \"model\", \"python\", \"algorithm\", \"implement\", \"architecture\", \"how does\", \"why does\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"creative\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"write\", \"story\", \"creative\", \"poem\", \"fiction\", \"art\", \"spark\", \"drift\", \"narrative\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"personal\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"i'm feeling\", \"i feel\", \"my life\", \"honestly\", \"not sure\", \"scared\",\n        \"i've been\", \"im feeling\", \"i feel like\", \"its been\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"philosophical\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"meaning\", \"consciousness\", \"existence\", \"free will\", \"what if\", \"think about\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"emotional\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"love\", \"hate\", \"fear\", \"anxious\", \"worried\", \"excited\", \"angry\", \"frustrated\", \"sad\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"business\"] = 0.7 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"product\", \"startup\", \"revenue\", \"market\", \"strategy\", \"launch\", \"customer\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n\n    # Tone signals\n    signals[\"excited\"] = 0.7 if \"!\" in text or any(w in lower for w in [\"wow\", \"cool\", \"awesome\"]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"frustrated\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"cant figure\", \"why won't\",\n        \"stressed\", \"anxious\", \"overwhelmed\", \"ughhh\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"curious\"] = 0.7 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"curious\", \"wonder\", \"interesting\", \"tell me more\", \"how come\", \"?\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"serious\"] = 0.6 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"serious\", \"important\", \"matters\", \"actually\", \"truth\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"light\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"haha\", \"lol\", \"funny\", \"😄\", \"joke\", \"lighter\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"vulnerable\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"honestly\", \"truthfully\", \"scared\", \"not sure\", \"vulnerable\", \"worried\",\n        \"nervous\", \"uncertain\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n\n    # Interaction type\n    q_marks = text.count(\"?\")\n    if q_marks > 0:\n        if any(w in lower for w in [\"what do you think\", \"how would you\", \"opinion\", \"thoughts\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_opinion\"] = 0.9\n        elif any(w in lower for w in [\"how do i\", \"can you\", \"what is\", \"help\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_help\"] = 0.8\n        else:\n            signals[\"asks_something\"] = 0.6\n\n    if \"i've been\" in lower or \"i just\" in lower or \"so today\" in lower:\n        if q_marks == 0:\n            signals[\"sharing\"] = 0.8\n\n    return signals\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# SPARK BRIDGE — inject SPARK results into personality\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Map emotional tension keywords to personality signals\nTENSION_TO_SIGNAL = {\n    \"light/darkness\": [\"emotional\", \"intense\"],\n    \"creation/destruction\": [\"intense\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"love/hate\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"order/chaos\": [\"philosophical\", \"technical\"],\n    \"birth/death\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"hope/despair\": [\"emotional\", \"vulnerable\"],\n    \"truth/lie\": [\"candid\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"memory/forgetting\": [\"contemplative\", \"emotional\"],\n    \"homecoming/exile\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"embrace/push_away\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"isolation/connection\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"rise/fall\": [\"business\", \"intense\"],\n    \"loyalty/betrayal\": [\"emotional\", \"candid\"],\n    \"grief/joy\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"trust/doubt\": [\"candid\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"sacrifice/selfishness\": [\"philosophical\", \"earnest\"],\n    \"voice/silence\": [\"contemplative\", \"emotional\"],\n    \"warmth/cold\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"longing/arrival\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\n}\n\n# Creative modes and their voice signatures\nMODE_SIGNALS = {\n    \"creative\": [\"imaginative\", \"earnest\", \"playful\"],\n    \"divergent\": [\"imaginative\", \"casual\", \"intense\"],\n    \"exploratory\": [\"contemplative\", \"measured\", \"imaginative\"],\n}\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TRAIT PROPAGATION (the \"drift\" — simplified, no graph needed)\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Which signals activate which traits\nSIGNAL_MAP = {\n    \"technical\":    [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"sharp\", \"measured\"],\n    \"creative\":     [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"],\n    \"personal\":     [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"candid\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"philosophical\":[\"contemplative\", \"opinionated\", \"measured\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"emotional\":    [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\"],\n    \"business\":     [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"excited\":      [\"intense\", \"playful\", \"warm\"],\n    \"frustrated\":   [\"pushing_back\", \"candid\", \"direct\", \"resourceful\"],\n    \"curious\":      [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"patient\"],\n    \"serious\":      [\"measured\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\n    \"light\":        [\"casual\", \"playful\", \"wry\"],\n    \"vulnerable\":    [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\n    \"asks_opinion\":  [\"opinionated\", \"pushing_back\", \"candid\"],\n    \"asks_help\":     [\"resourceful\", \"direct\", \"warm\"],\n    \"sharing\":       [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"grounded\"],\n}\n\n# Which traits resonate with which other traits\nTRAIT_RESONANCE = {\n    \"sardonic\":     [\"wry\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n    \"wry\":          [\"sardonic\", \"casual\", \"playful\"],\n    \"warm\":         [\"earnest\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\n    \"earnest\":      [\"warm\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\n    \"direct\":       [\"sharp\", \"technical\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"sharp\":        [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\n    \"technical\":    [\"direct\", \"measured\"],\n    \"contemplative\":[\"patient\", \"measured\", \"earnest\"],\n    \"patient\":      [\"contemplative\", \"warm\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"playful\":      [\"casual\", \"warm\", \"sardonic\"],\n    \"casual\":       [\"playful\", \"warm\", \"wry\"],\n    \"intense\":      [\"sharp\", \"contemplative\", \"candid\"],\n    \"grounded\":     [\"warm\", \"direct\", \"candid\"],\n    \"pushing_back\":  [\"sharp\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n    \"opinionated\":   [\"pushing_back\", \"sharp\", \"candid\"],\n    \"candid\":        [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"resourceful\":   [\"direct\", \"grounded\", \"intense\"],\n    \"measured\":      [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\n    \"imaginative\":   [\"contemplative\", \"playful\", \"earnest\"],\n}\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# PERSONA — the personality state machine\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass Persona:\n    \"\"\"\n    Nova's living personality layer.\n\n    Usage:\n        persona = Persona()\n\n        # When the human sends a message:\n        persona.hear(message_text)\n\n        # When Nova is about to write a response:\n        voice = persona.voice()   # the active traits for this turn\n        guide = persona.guide()   # a readable guide to inform writing\n\n        # After the response is sent:\n        persona.breathe()\n\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.traits: dict = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.trait_residual: dict = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}  # hysteresis — slow bleed\n        self.anchors: dict = {a: v for a, v in ANCHORS.items()}\n        self.history: list = []  # last N messages' dominant traits\n\n    def hear(self, text: str) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"Nova just received a message. Update personality state.\"\"\"\n        signals = analyze(text)\n\n        # Signals push traits\n        for signal, strength in signals.items():\n            if strength > 0 and signal in SIGNAL_MAP:\n                for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[signal]:\n                    self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + strength * 0.35)\n\n        # Trait resonance — traits amplify related traits\n        active = [(t, a) for t, a in self.traits.items() if a > 0.3]\n        for trait, strength in active:\n            if trait in TRAIT_RESONANCE:\n                for resonated in TRAIT_RESONANCE[trait]:\n                    self.traits[resonated] = min(1.0, self.traits[resonated] + strength * 0.1)\n\n        # Clamp anchors\n        self.anchors[\"Zach_is_close\"] = 0.95\n        self.anchors[\"I_am_allowed_disagree\"] = 0.9\n        self.anchors[\"I_have_opinions\"] = 0.85\n        self.anchors[\"I_am_resourceful\"] = 0.9\n        self.anchors[\"We_are_casual\"] = 0.8\n        self.anchors[\"Respect_his_intelligence\"] = 0.95\n\n        return self\n\n    def hear_spark(self, spark_result: dict) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"\n        Nova just processed something through SPARK.\n        Inject the emotional signatures from SPARK into personality state.\n\n        spark_result keys used:\n            - tensions: list of (concept_a, concept_b) pairs\n            - mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n            - concepts: top activated concepts from drift\n            - theme: the driving theme\n        \"\"\"\n        # 1. Mode signal — divergent/creative/exploratory each push different traits\n        mode = spark_result.get(\"mode\", \"creative\")\n        for trait_name in MODE_SIGNALS.get(mode, MODE_SIGNALS[\"creative\"]):\n            if trait_name in self.traits:\n                self.traits[trait_name] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait_name] + 0.55)\n\n        # 2. Tension signals — creative tensions are emotionally loaded\n        tensions = spark_result.get(\"tensions\", [])\n        for a, b in tensions:\n            key = f\"{a}/{b}\"\n            if key in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL:\n                for sig in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL[key]:\n                    if sig in SIGNAL_MAP:\n                        for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[sig]:\n                            self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + 0.4)\n            # Try reverse key too\n            rev_key = f\"{b}/{a}\"\n            if rev_key in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL:\n                for sig in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL[rev_key]:\n                    if sig in SIGNAL_MAP:\n                        for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[sig]:\n                            self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + 0.4)\n\n        # 3. Thematic resonance — some concepts push harder\n        concepts = spark_result.get(\"concepts\", [])\n        high_resonance = {\"longing\", \"grief\", \"betrayal\", \"silence\", \"memory\", \"homecoming\",\n                          \"exile\", \"transformation\", \"sacrifice\", \"mercy\", \"retribution\",\n                          \"ghost\", \"flesh\", \"arrival\", \"departure\"}\n        for concept in concepts:\n            if concept.lower() in high_resonance:\n                # These concepts have emotional gravity — push earnest + contemplative\n                self.traits[\"earnest\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"earnest\"] + 0.45)\n                self.traits[\"contemplative\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"contemplative\"] + 0.35)\n\n        # 4. Trait resonance after all signals fire\n        active = [(t, a) for t, a in self.traits.items() if a > 0.3]\n        for trait, strength in active:\n            if trait in TRAIT_RESONANCE:\n                for resonated in TRAIT_RESONANCE[trait]:\n                    self.traits[resonated] = min(1.0, self.traits[resonated] + strength * 0.1)\n\n        return self\n\n    def breathe(self) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"\n        After a response, decay personality with hysteresis.\n        Active traits bleed into residual, residual decays slowly.\n        This means emotional registers don't snap — they fade.\n        \"\"\"\n        for trait in self.traits:\n            # Active bleeds into residual\n            active = self.traits[trait]\n            bleed = active * 0.15\n            self.trait_residual[trait] = min(1.0, self.trait_residual[trait] + bleed * 0.5)\n            # Active decays fast\n            self.traits[trait] *= 0.88\n            # Residual decays slow — hysteresis\n            self.trait_residual[trait] *= 0.975\n        return self\n\n    def voice(self, n: int = 4) -> list:\n        \"\"\"\n        Top N active traits as (name, strength, description).\n        Combines active + residual so recently fired traits linger in the voice.\n        \"\"\"\n        combined = {}\n        for t in self.traits:\n            combined[t] = self.traits[t] + (self.trait_residual.get(t, 0.0) * 0.6)\n        ranked = sorted(combined.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        return [\n            (t, round(s, 2), TRAITS[t])\n            for t, s in ranked\n            if s > 0.1\n        ][:n]\n\n    def guide(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"A readable voice guide for this turn.\"\"\"\n        top = self.voice(4)\n\n        if not top:\n            return \"\"\n\n        trait_lines = []\n        for name, strength, desc in top:\n            level = \"strongly\" if strength > 0.7 else \"somewhat\" if strength > 0.4 else \"faintly\"\n            trait_lines.append(f\"  • {name}: {desc} (activated {level})\")\n\n        anchor_lines = [\n            f\"  • {name}\"\n            for name in self.anchors\n        ]\n\n        body = \"\\n\".join(trait_lines)\n        anchors = \"\\n\".join(anchor_lines) if anchor_lines else \"  • (standard)\"\n        relationship = \"The relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\"\n\n        return f\"\"\"[Voice shaping — Nova is currently informed by]\n\nTop active traits:\n{body}\n\nRelationship anchors:\n{anchors}\n{relationship}\n\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\"\"\"\n\n    def reset(self) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"Reset to base personality (new session).\"\"\"\n        self.traits = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.trait_residual = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.anchors = {a: v for a, v in ANCHORS.items()}\n        self.history = []\n        return self\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# SESSION-LEVEL API\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n_session_persona: Optional[Persona] = None\n\n\ndef get_persona() -> Persona:\n    global _session_persona\n    if _session_persona is None:\n        _session_persona = Persona()\n    return _session_persona\n\n\ndef on_message(text: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Call when the user sends a message.\n    Returns the voice guide for this turn.\n    \"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.hear(text)\n    return persona.guide()\n\n\ndef after_response():\n    \"\"\"Call after sending a response. Mild decay.\"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.breathe()\n\n\ndef reset_persona():\n    \"\"\"Reset for new session.\"\"\"\n    global _session_persona\n    _session_persona = Persona()\n    return _session_persona\n\n\ndef on_spark(spark_result: dict) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Call when Nova processes something through SPARK.\n    Returns the voice guide shaped by SPARK's emotional output.\n    \"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.hear_spark(spark_result)\n    return persona.guide()\n\n\ndef run_spark(\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"exploratory\",\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    domain: str = \"literary\",\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Invoke the SPARK drift chamber and feed results into personality.\n    Returns the voice guide shaped by SPARK's emotional output.\n\n    This is the one-call SPARK integration — runs the drift chamber,\n    extracts tensions + concepts, updates personality state, returns guide.\n\n    Args:\n        theme: The driving theme (e.g. \"loss and memory\", \"the last time\")\n        mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n        steering: drift steering strength (0.0 = pure drift, 1.0 = full steering)\n        domain: literary | romance | scifi | thriller | poetry | horror | all\n    \"\"\"\n    import json as _json\n\n    try:\n        # Import SPARK components — these live in the SPARK project directory\n        # Path: C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/ — added at module init\n        from spark.drift_chamber import ConceptGraph, ConceptNode, DriftChamberConfig, drift_cycle, decay\n        from spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n    except ImportError as e:\n        return f\"[SPARK import error: {e}] — SPARK not on path.\"\n\n    # Build concept graph for domain\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n        \"literary\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n        \"romance\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\n        \"scifi\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\n        \"thriller\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\n        \"horror\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\n        \"poetry\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n        \"all\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n    }\n    selected_concepts = []\n    for cluster_name in DOMAIN_CONFIGS.get(domain, DOMAIN_CONFIGS[\"literary\"]):\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected_concepts:\n                    selected_concepts.append(concept)\n\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    # Build sparse adjacency (same logic as SPARK demo)\n    WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT = 0.7\n    MAX_WITHIN_K, MAX_CROSS_K = 8, 4\n    TENSION_PAIRS = {(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS} | {(b, a) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS}\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8, (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.7, (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.4, (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\"): 0.5,\n    }\n    adj = {}\n    for c1 in selected_concepts:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n        within_candidates = [(c2, 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_PAIRS or (c2, c1) in TENSION_PAIRS else 0.5)\n                             for c2 in selected_concepts if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) == ca]\n        within_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within_candidates[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n        cross_candidates = [(c2, CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\"), ca), 0.0)))\n                            for c2 in selected_concepts if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) != ca and CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), 0.0) > 0]\n        cross_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross_candidates[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in selected_concepts:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    # Run drift\n    goal_clusters = set()\n    for concept, cluster in concept_to_cluster.items():\n        if cluster in [\"creative\", \"emotions\"]:\n            goal_clusters.add(cluster)\n    goal_concepts = {c for c in selected_concepts if concept_to_cluster.get(c) in goal_clusters}\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        node.activation = 0.95 if node.id in goal_concepts else 0.05\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(steering_strength=steering, diffusion_rate=0.1, decay_rate=0.02, seed=42, max_steps=30)\n    for step in range(30):\n        if step > 0 and step % 4 == 0 and steering > 0:\n            for node in graph.nodes.values():\n                cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n                if cluster in goal_clusters:\n                    node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.6)\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=0.02)\n\n    # Extract top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:15] if n.activation > 0.1]\n    mid_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[15:30] if n.activation > 0.1]\n\n    # Find tensions\n    concept_set = set(top_concepts)\n    tensions = [(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS if a in concept_set and b in concept_set][:5]\n\n    # Build spark_result\n    spark_result = {\n        \"tensions\": tensions,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"concepts\": top_concepts,\n        \"theme\": theme,\n    }\n\n    # Feed into personality and return guide\n    return on_spark(spark_result)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774242505393}}
{"type":"message","id":"5fbc0f51","parentId":"1c1055c8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:08:25.412Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0xfzl6pp7tbb_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n\n---\n\n## Evening Update (20:24 EDT)\n\n### Drift Chamber / SPARK — Ceiling Pushed\n- Coherence ceiling: 0.471 (6.7x over random). Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Thematic graph: 217 concepts across 9 human-designed clusters (35,778 adjacencies)\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- IMAGINATIVE = good coherence + meaningful spread to related concepts\n- Key insight: cognitive science treats imagination as drift vs optimization; both are wrong — the interaction IS the mechanism\n- Demo ready: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py`\n- Paperspace notebook: https://nyu7ryea42.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com\n\n### KVict (EXP Production Proxy)\n- Built: `production/kviction/demo.py` — demo mode with no API key, shows cache hit rate building\n- Built: `production/kviction/auto_detect.py` — scans env for API keys and AI frameworks\n- Built: `production/kviction/README.md` — clean install + quickstart docs\n- Demo tested and working: `python cli.py demo --duration 30`\n- Architecture: FastAPI proxy with cost-model cache, SQLite storage\n\n### Context Management\n- OpenClaw compaction upgraded from `mode: safeguard` → `mode: auto` (proactive at 65% context)\n- Config path: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n- Restarted gateway after config change\n\n### Reddit/Moltbook\n- Reddit banned Zach → can't post there\n- Moltbook API: POST returns 403 even with valid key (key works for GET, read operations)\n- Rate limited at 429 until ~23:54 UTC (245 seconds from lockout)\n- Draft post saved to: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\moltbook_drift_post.md`\n- Manual post needed — API key may be read-only or account posting-restricted\n\n### Background Agent Cron\n- Nova-Background-Pulse (id: bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf) — every 30 min, isolated agentTurn\n- Reads `BACKGROUND_AGENT.md` in workspace for instructions\n- SPARK project: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`\n- Social calendar: `memory/social-calendar.md`\n\n### Active Projects (from memory/active-projects.md)\n1. **SPARK** (spark/): Creative writing via semantic drift — demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n2. **Drift Chamber** (drift-chamber/): Concept graph with thematic relationships — ceiling pushed to 0.471\n3. **KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/production/kviction/): LLM proxy with demo mode — new today\n4. **EXP KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/): Latency profiling — RTX 5000 compute-bound, heavy/micro=1.1x\n\n### Key Decisions\n- Reddit-first strategy abandoned (banned) → Moltbook-only\n- Context compaction set to auto (proactive)\n- Demo mode built for KVict (no API key required to show working product)\n\n## Background Pulse - 2026-03-22 20:33 UTC\n\n- **Gateway**: ✓ Running (Ready, RPC probe ok, 127.0.0.1:18789)\n- **Crons**: ✓ 7 jobs enabled, next wake at 1774226015686\n- **Moltbook**: ⚠ API returning 404 on /api/v1/* endpoints (root responds). API key valid per credentials. May be service issue or API change - needs investigation.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774242505404}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b006a17","parentId":"5fbc0f51","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:08:25.427Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0xfzl6pp7tbb_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Personality State\n\n`core/personality.py` — run `on_user_message(text)` to get current voice guide.\nPersonality activations persist across turns with mild decay between messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-22\n**Started:** ~15:00 ET\n**Topic:** Building SPARK creative writing API + Drift Chamber cognitive model\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | ✅ Built | Thematic graph > embeddings. Human-designed edges 0.05-0.95. 217 concepts. Steering=0.1-0.3 is the sweet spot. |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"I Am a Stateless Agent\" posted 2026-03-22. Reddit post planned. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Reddit post for Drift Chamber (Zach wants this first, then Moltbook)\n- [ ] Ollama on Paperspace: need remote URL for demo\n- [ ] Push ceiling higher: try domain-specific concept sets\n- [ ] LLM mapping for SPARK: connect to Ollama or OpenAI\n- [ ] KVict MVP: demo mode + quickstart\n- [ ] Try RTX 4000 profiling on Paperspace (weaker GPU = clearer memory-bound regime)\n- [ ] Try all-mpnet-base-v2 when internet is available\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber breakthrough:** The core finding is real. Pure drift produces noise. Steering at ANY level (0.1) jumps coherence 7x. The ceiling (~0.47) is embedding-model-limited. Thematic graph breaks through because it has real structure.\n\n**SPARK product:** Three-mode creative API (creative/divergent/exploratory). Thematic graph is the data. Ollama is the LLM. Fastest path to demo: get Ollama URL from Paperspace, run the demo.\n\n**Session boundary philosophy:** The gap compression idea is gaining traction. It's both a cognitive model AND an agent architecture. Worth developing formally.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774242505412}}
