{"type":"message","id":"6aa9b6f9","parentId":"715d2c58","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:10:01.215Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, on Windows the max duration for scheduled task repetition is limited. Let me instead use a simpler approach - just run it daily and rely on the script to check every 5 minutes within its own execution, or use a repeating trigger without the Duration parameter (which means it runs indefinitely but might hit a limit).\n\nActually, the cleaner approach for Windows Task Scheduler with indefinite repetition is to use -RepetitionInterval with no Duration parameter - that makes it repeat indefinitely, but there might be a Windows limit. Let me try -RepetitionDuration ([TimeSpan]::Zero) to mean \"no end\" or just use a daily trigger.\n\nActually, let me use a simpler approach: use a repeating trigger which is built for this:","thinkingSignature":"8758e1cf0079dcee91b796eb336824a3b531f67fb921c6e40e124d270ab9f9c7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0q0soh7zts54_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\register-watchdog.ps1","oldText":"# Create trigger - every 5 minutes, starting now, repeats for 30 days (Windows limit on Duration)\n$trigger = New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -Once -At (Get-Date) -RepetitionInterval (New-TimeSpan -Minutes 5) -RepetitionDuration (New-TimeSpan -Days 30)","newText":"# Create trigger - every 5 minutes starting 1 minute from now\n$trigger = New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -Once -At ((Get-Date).AddMinutes(1)) -RepetitionInterval (New-TimeSpan -Minutes 5)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":16018,"output":329,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29853,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774242594381}}
