{"type":"message","id":"548e715a","parentId":"f8d297ab","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:12:28.376Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at health.md to find the correct health check endpoint.","thinkingSignature":"2686ddac5a3e593995c2de0e188d78d746ea562920f5bf5eaf19fe34393f1cdc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kwhogf6ssntq_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\health.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21664,"output":64,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35234,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774242746004}}
{"type":"message","id":"39ded17a","parentId":"548e715a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:12:28.403Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kwhogf6ssntq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Health check steps for channel connectivity\"\nread_when:\n  - Diagnosing WhatsApp channel health\ntitle: \"Health Checks\"\n---\n\n# Health Checks (CLI)\n\nShort guide to verify channel connectivity without guessing.\n\n## Quick checks\n\n- `openclaw status` — local summary: gateway reachability/mode, update hint, linked channel auth age, sessions + recent activity.\n- `openclaw status --all` — full local diagnosis (read-only, color, safe to paste for debugging).\n- `openclaw status --deep` — also probes the running Gateway (per-channel probes when supported).\n- `openclaw health --json` — asks the running Gateway for a full health snapshot (WS-only; no direct Baileys socket).\n- Send `/status` as a standalone message in WhatsApp/WebChat to get a status reply without invoking the agent.\n- Logs: tail `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-*.log` and filter for `web-heartbeat`, `web-reconnect`, `web-auto-reply`, `web-inbound`.\n\n## Deep diagnostics\n\n- Creds on disk: `ls -l ~/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/<accountId>/creds.json` (mtime should be recent).\n- Session store: `ls -l ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/sessions.json` (path can be overridden in config). Count and recent recipients are surfaced via `status`.\n- Relink flow: `openclaw channels logout && openclaw channels login --verbose` when status codes 409–515 or `loggedOut` appear in logs. (Note: the QR login flow auto-restarts once for status 515 after pairing.)\n\n## When something fails\n\n- `logged out` or status 409–515 → relink with `openclaw channels logout` then `openclaw channels login`.\n- Gateway unreachable → start it: `openclaw gateway --port 18789` (use `--force` if the port is busy).\n- No inbound messages → confirm linked phone is online and the sender is allowed (`channels.whatsapp.allowFrom`); for group chats, ensure allowlist + mention rules match (`channels.whatsapp.groups`, `agents.list[].groupChat.mentionPatterns`).\n\n## Dedicated \"health\" command\n\n`openclaw health --json` asks the running Gateway for its health snapshot (no direct channel sockets from the CLI). It reports linked creds/auth age when available, per-channel probe summaries, session-store summary, and a probe duration. It exits non-zero if the Gateway is unreachable or the probe fails/timeouts. Use `--timeout <ms>` to override the 10s default.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774242748393}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c6adaf8","parentId":"39ded17a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:12:42.837Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the `openclaw health --json` command asks the running Gateway for its health snapshot. The RPC endpoint is likely a WebSocket endpoint, not HTTP. Let me look at the health probe more closely.\n\nActually, for the watchdog, the simplest approach is just to check if the gateway process is running. The RPC check was overly complex. Let me simplify the watchdog to just check if the gateway process is running (by checking if `openclaw gateway status` works, or by checking the process).\n\nActually, since `openclaw status` works and the gateway is running, the simplest health check for the watchdog would be to just call `openclaw health --json` and check if it succeeds. \n\nNow I'll update the watchdog script to use this approach.","thinkingSignature":"5a128a6d8b91f3dc68cc9178e3227593703d938d6873fe3171610adf4f438827"},{"type":"text","text":"The gateway health check uses `openclaw health --json`. Let me update the watchdog to use the proper check:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ki2hf3buuu1e_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1","content":"# gateway-watchdog.ps1\n# Checks if OpenClaw gateway is running, restarts it if not.\n# Run via Task Scheduler every 5 minutes.\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\n$LogPath = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\logs\\watchdog.log\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\n$logDir = Split-Path $logPath -Parent\nif (!(Test-Path $logDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $logDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log {\n    param([string]$Message)\n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    \"$timestamp $Message\" | Add-Content -Path $logPath -Encoding UTF8\n}\n\n# Check gateway health using openclaw CLI\n$healthOutput = & openclaw health --json 2>&1\n$healthExit = $LASTEXITCODE\n\nif ($healthExit -eq 0) {\n    Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is healthy\"\n    exit 0\n}\n\nWrite-Log \"WARN: Gateway unhealthy (exit $healthExit). Output: $healthOutput\"\n\n# Try to restart\ntry {\n    # Kill any stale node processes related to openclaw\n    $staleProcesses = Get-Process -Name \"node\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object {\n        $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*gateway*\" -or $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*\"\n    }\n    if ($staleProcesses) {\n        foreach ($proc in $staleProcesses) {\n            Write-Log \"Stopping stale process: $($proc.Id)\"\n            Stop-Process -Id $proc.Id -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        }\n        Start-Sleep -Seconds 3\n    }\n\n    # Start gateway\n    Write-Log \"INFO: Starting gateway...\"\n    Start-Process -FilePath \"openclaw\" -ArgumentList \"gateway start\" -WindowStyle Minimized -PassThru | Out-Null\n\n    # Wait for startup\n    Start-Sleep -Seconds 10\n\n    # Verify\n    $verifyOutput = & openclaw health --json 2>&1\n    if ($LASTEXITCODE -eq 0) {\n        Write-Log \"SUCCESS: Gateway restarted and healthy\"\n        exit 0\n    } else {\n        Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restarted but health check still failing\"\n        exit 1\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"ERROR: Exception during restart: $_\"\n    exit 1\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22286,"output":765,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774242748404}}
