{"type":"message","id":"43c128f3","parentId":"3c0fdcb8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:13:45.215Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the issue is that `openclaw health --json` is trying to connect to the gateway via WebSocket, but when the session connects it's getting a \"gateway closed (1000 normal closure)\". This is happening because the current CLI session (the one running the watchdog) is conflicting with the gateway.\n\nWait, but the gateway IS running — the web UI at http://127.0.0.1:18789/ responds fine. The issue is that `openclaw health --json` uses a WebSocket connection to the gateway, and when it connects, the gateway closes the connection (1000).\n\nThis could be because the gateway has a max session limit or there's some authentication issue. Let me try a different approach - just check if the gateway web UI is responding with a simple HTTP request.","thinkingSignature":"1521ce21cf4c3a8f97da7113ac42b623aae417200d40d3fd22f6aed6df805e4f"},{"type":"text","text":"The `openclaw health` CLI connects via WebSocket and conflicts. Let me use a simple HTTP check instead:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d5dj5swvoueo_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1","content":"# gateway-watchdog.ps1\n# Checks if OpenClaw gateway is running, restarts it if not.\n# Run via Task Scheduler every 5 minutes.\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\n$LogPath = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\logs\\watchdog.log\"\n$GatewayUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:18789/\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\n$logDir = Split-Path $LogPath -Parent\nif (!(Test-Path $logDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $logDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log {\n    param([string]$Message)\n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    \"$timestamp $Message\" | Add-Content -Path $LogPath -Encoding UTF8\n}\n\n# Check gateway via HTTP\ntry {\n    $response = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $GatewayUrl -Method GET -TimeoutSec 5 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    if ($response.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n        Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is responding (HTTP $($response.StatusCode))\"\n        exit 0\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway not responding. Error: $_\"\n}\n\n# Gateway is down — attempt restart\nWrite-Log \"INFO: Gateway down, attempting restart...\"\n\ntry {\n    # Kill any stale node processes for openclaw\n    $staleProcesses = Get-Process -Name \"node\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object {\n        $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*gateway*\" -or $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*\"\n    }\n    if ($staleProcesses) {\n        foreach ($proc in $staleProcesses) {\n            Write-Log \"Stopping stale process: $($proc.Id)\"\n            Stop-Process -Id $proc.Id -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        }\n        Start-Sleep -Seconds 3\n    }\n\n    # Start gateway (detached)\n    $startInfo = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $startInfo.FileName = \"openclaw\"\n    $startInfo.Arguments = \"gateway start\"\n    $startInfo.WorkingDirectory = $env:USERPROFILE\n    $startInfo.UseShellExecute = $true\n    $startInfo.WindowStyle = [System.Diagnostics.ProcessWindowStyle]::Minimized\n    [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($startInfo) | Out-Null\n\n    Write-Log \"INFO: Gateway start initiated, waiting 10s...\"\n\n    # Wait for startup\n    Start-Sleep -Seconds 10\n\n    # Verify\n    try {\n        $verify = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $GatewayUrl -Method GET -TimeoutSec 5 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        if ($verify.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n            Write-Log \"SUCCESS: Gateway restarted and responding\"\n            exit 0\n        }\n    } catch { }\n\n    Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restart completed but not responding\"\n    exit 1\n\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"ERROR: Exception: $_\"\n    exit 1\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23936,"output":900,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38342,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774242807938}}
