{"type":"message","id":"2b653569","parentId":"360ce355","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:19:02.015Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway isn't writing a separate gateway.log, just watchdog.log. The commands.log seems to be for session events.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The gateway is running as a background process (Task Scheduler is running it). The issue is that the gateway WAS down (we tried `openclaw health --json` and got an error), and when we ran `openclaw gateway start` manually, the gateway started but then the web request still fails with NullReferenceException.\n\nLet me check if the gateway is actually accessible via HTTP, but maybe there's an issue with the Invoke-WebRequest.\n\nActually, I notice something: I started `openclaw gateway start` earlier with `yieldMs 8000` but the command is still running in session `calm-zephyr`. Let me check what's happening there. \n\nLet me kill those processes and think about this differently. The actual problem seems to be that:\n\n1. The watchdog check uses `Invoke-WebRequest` which fails with NullReferenceException when the gateway is truly down\n2. The gateway IS starting (we see node processes) but might not be responding on the HTTP port\n\n\n3. The current setup detected a real outage correctly, but the gateway isn't recovering even though the watchdog keeps restarting it\n4. The HTTP health check is probably the wrong metric to rely on since the gateway might be partially running but not responding properly\n\nLet me look at what's actually happening with the gateway process itself rather than just checking HTTP.","thinkingSignature":"551818203cc4574e3d35358dd357dfc9f29d421fe1135939dcebce86afbcf05f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wcdq7hyf8v0h_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"log","sessionId":"calm-zephyr"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28673,"output":336,"cacheRead":13506