{"type":"message","id":"d7c6c947","parentId":"2949d146","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:19:29.460Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"HTTP 200. The gateway IS up. The issue was with `Invoke-WebRequest` in PowerShell giving a NullReferenceException (which is a PowerShell bug when the connection fails in certain ways), while `curl` works fine.\n\nSo the watchdog script IS working now. Let me update the watchdog script to use `curl` instead of `Invoke-WebRequest`, then verify the scheduled task is running properly with the new script.","thinkingSignature":"50467449f33ed3cd253517bc0d8661d60dc3a91df869166249ef052d242e2e85"},{"type":"text","text":"HTTP 200 — gateway's up. The `Invoke-WebRequest` PowerShell bug was giving false negatives. Let me fix the watchdog to use `curl` instead:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9nsb6hmsssze_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1","oldText":"# Check gateway via HTTP\ntry {\n    $response = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $GatewayUrl -Method GET -TimeoutSec 5 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    if ($response.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n        Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is responding (HTTP $($response.StatusCode))\"\n        exit 0\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway not responding. Error: $_\"\n}","newText":"# Check gateway via HTTP using curl (more reliable than Invoke-WebRequest)\ntry {\n    $statusCode = curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\n    if ($statusCode -eq \"200\") {\n        Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is responding (HTTP 200)\"\n        exit 0\n    } else {\n        Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway returned HTTP $statusCode\"\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway not responding. Error: $_\"\n}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29617,"output":392,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43515,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243160946}}
{"type":"message","id":"84553d7a","parentId":"d7c6c947","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:19:29.488Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9nsb6hmsssze_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 17     $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n 18     \"$timestamp $Message\" | Add-Content -Path $LogPath -Encoding UTF8\n 19 }\n 20 \n-21 # Check gateway via HTTP\n+21 # Check gateway via HTTP using curl (more reliable than Invoke-WebRequest)\n 22 try {\n-23     $response = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $GatewayUrl -Method GET -TimeoutSec 5 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n-24     if ($response.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n-25         Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is responding (HTTP $($response.StatusCode))\"\n+23     $statusCode = curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\n+24     if ($statusCode -eq \"200\") {\n+25         Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is responding (HTTP 200)\"\n 26         exit 0\n+27     } else {\n+28         Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway returned HTTP $statusCode\"\n 27     }\n 28 } catch {\n 29     Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway not responding. Error: $_\"\n 30 }\n    ...","firstChangedLine":21},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243169475}}
{"type":"message","id":"858163cb","parentId":"84553d7a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:19:35.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also update the verify section to use curl.","thinkingSignature":"4c6c1e1b8310450b0a8c43176636c810db14df0808ee5c5545abf01a4452c301"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yqyfhcdhcghi_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1","oldText":"    # Verify\n    try {\n        $verify = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $GatewayUrl -Method GET -TimeoutSec 5 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        if ($verify.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n            Write-Log \"SUCCESS: Gateway restarted and responding\"\n            exit 0\n        }\n    } catch { }\n\n    Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restart completed but not responding\"\n    exit 1","newText":"    # Verify with curl\n    Start-Sleep 3\n    try {\n        $verifyStatus = curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\n        if ($verifyStatus -eq \"200\") {\n            Write-Log \"SUCCESS: Gateway restarted and responding\"\n            exit 0\n        } else {\n            Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restarted but returned HTTP $verifyStatus\"\n        }\n    } catch {\n        Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restart verification failed\"\n    }\n    exit 1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30048,"output":277,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43831,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243169491}}
{"type":"message","id":"19115c6f","parentId":"858163cb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:19:35.635Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yqyfhcdhcghi_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 60 \n 61     # Wait for startup\n 62     Start-Sleep -Seconds 10\n 63 \n-64     # Verify\n+64     # Verify with curl\n+65     Start-Sleep 3\n 65     try {\n-66         $verify = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $GatewayUrl -Method GET -TimeoutSec 5 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n-67         if ($verify.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n+67         $verifyStatus = curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\n+68         if ($verifyStatus -eq \"200\") {\n 68             Write-Log \"SUCCESS: Gateway restarted and responding\"\n 69             exit 0\n+71         } else {\n+72             Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restarted but returned HTTP $verifyStatus\"\n 70         }\n-71     } catch { }\n-72 \n-73     Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restart completed but not responding\"\n+74     } catch {\n+75         Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restart verification failed\"\n+76     }\n 74     exit 1\n 75 \n 76 } catch {\n 77     Write-Log \"ERROR: Exception: $_\"\n    ...","firstChangedLine":64},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243175620}}
