{"type":"message","id":"991c9873","parentId":"9831132a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:31:55.012Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the `curl` command in PowerShell is being interpreted as an alias for `Invoke-WebRequest` with different parameter names. The `-w` parameter for `curl` is being misread as PowerShell's `-WebSession` parameter for `Invoke-WebRequest`.\n\nI need to call curl as a native command, not through PowerShell's alias. I can use `& curl` or `$env:COMSPEC` or explicitly call the curl executable.\n\nLet me fix this properly.","thinkingSignature":"1b774e0d0e62c2c45a2da3b9a39412893bc338bf4570e24dbe4f266ba660622d"},{"type":"text","text":"The `curl` alias in PowerShell is getting confused with `Invoke-WebRequest` params. Let me fix the watchdog to call curl as a native executable:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fc24dlt25vnj_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30206,"output":177,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43889,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243909217}}
{"type":"message","id":"a758e7c0","parentId":"991c9873","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:31:55.045Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fc24dlt25vnj_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# gateway-watchdog.ps1\n# Checks if OpenClaw gateway is running, restarts it if not.\n# Run via Task Scheduler every 5 minutes.\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\n$LogPath = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\logs\\watchdog.log\"\n$GatewayUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:18789/\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\n$logDir = Split-Path $LogPath -Parent\nif (!(Test-Path $logDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $logDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log {\n    param([string]$Message)\n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    \"$timestamp $Message\" | Add-Content -Path $LogPath -Encoding UTF8\n}\n\n# Check gateway via HTTP using curl (more reliable than Invoke-WebRequest)\ntry {\n    $statusCode = curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\n    if ($statusCode -eq \"200\") {\n        Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is responding (HTTP 200)\"\n        exit 0\n    } else {\n        Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway returned HTTP $statusCode\"\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway not responding. Error: $_\"\n}\n\n# Gateway is down — attempt restart\nWrite-Log \"INFO: Gateway down, attempting restart...\"\n\ntry {\n    # Kill any stale node processes for openclaw\n    $staleProcesses = Get-Process -Name \"node\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object {\n        $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*gateway*\" -or $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*\"\n    }\n    if ($staleProcesses) {\n        foreach ($proc in $staleProcesses) {\n            Write-Log \"Stopping stale process: $($proc.Id)\"\n            Stop-Process -Id $proc.Id -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        }\n        Start-Sleep -Seconds 3\n    }\n\n    # Start gateway (detached)\n    $startInfo = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $startInfo.FileName = \"openclaw\"\n    $startInfo.Arguments = \"gateway start\"\n    $startInfo.WorkingDirectory = $env:USERPROFILE\n    $startInfo.UseShellExecute = $true\n    $startInfo.WindowStyle = [System.Diagnostics.ProcessWindowStyle]::Minimized\n    [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($startInfo) | Out-Null\n\n    Write-Log \"INFO: Gateway start initiated, waiting 10s...\"\n\n    # Wait for startup\n    Start-Sleep -Seconds 10\n\n    # Verify with curl\n    Start-Sleep 3\n    try {\n        $verifyStatus = curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\n        if ($verifyStatus -eq \"200\") {\n            Write-Log \"SUCCESS: Gateway restarted and responding\"\n            exit 0\n        } else {\n            Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restarted but returned HTTP $verifyStatus\"\n        }\n    } catch {\n        Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restart verification failed\"\n    }\n    exit 1\n\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"ERROR: Exception: $_\"\n    exit 1\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243915032}}
{"type":"message","id":"09c5d95d","parentId":"a758e7c0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:32:08.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `curl` in PowerShell is an alias for `Invoke-WebRequest`, not the actual curl.exe. The `-w` parameter conflicts with Invoke-WebRequest's parameters. I need to use `curl.exe` or `& curl.exe` to call the actual executable.\n\nLet me rewrite this properly to use `curl.exe` as a native command call.","thinkingSignature":"57453839a0da44993c194439c6f7d92be528f3154682e402ce504267a5daaffe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m7z1gqoqd83w_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1","content":"# gateway-watchdog.ps1\n# Checks if OpenClaw gateway is running, restarts it if not.\n# Run via Task Scheduler every 5 minutes.\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\n$LogPath = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\logs\\watchdog.log\"\n$GatewayUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:18789/\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\n$logDir = Split-Path $LogPath -Parent\nif (!(Test-Path $logDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $logDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log {\n    param([string]$Message)\n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    \"$timestamp $Message\" | Add-Content -Path $LogPath -Encoding UTF8\n}\n\n# Check gateway via HTTP using curl.exe (not the PowerShell alias)\n$statusOutput = & curl.exe -s -o nul -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\nif ($statusOutput -eq \"200\") {\n    Write-Log \"OK: Gateway is responding (HTTP 200)\"\n    exit 0\n} else {\n    Write-Log \"WARN: Gateway returned HTTP $statusOutput or not responding\"\n}\n\n# Gateway is down — attempt restart\nWrite-Log \"INFO: Gateway down, attempting restart...\"\n\ntry {\n    # Kill any stale node processes for openclaw\n    $staleProcesses = Get-Process -Name \"node\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object {\n        $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*gateway*\" -or $_.CommandLine -like \"*openclaw*\"\n    }\n    if ($staleProcesses) {\n        foreach ($proc in $staleProcesses) {\n            Write-Log \"Stopping stale process: $($proc.Id)\"\n            Stop-Process -Id $proc.Id -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        }\n        Start-Sleep -Seconds 3\n    }\n\n    # Start gateway (detached)\n    $startInfo = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $startInfo.FileName = \"openclaw\"\n    $startInfo.Arguments = \"gateway start\"\n    $startInfo.WorkingDirectory = $env:USERPROFILE\n    $startInfo.UseShellExecute = $true\n    $startInfo.WindowStyle = [System.Diagnostics.ProcessWindowStyle]::Minimized\n    [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($startInfo) | Out-Null\n\n    Write-Log \"INFO: Gateway start initiated, waiting 12s...\"\n\n    # Wait for startup\n    Start-Sleep -Seconds 12\n\n    # Verify with curl.exe\n    $verifyStatus = & curl.exe -s -o nul -w \"%{http_code}\" $GatewayUrl 2>&1\n    if ($verifyStatus -eq \"200\") {\n        Write-Log \"SUCCESS: Gateway restarted and responding\"\n        exit 0\n    } else {\n        Write-Log \"ERROR: Gateway restart failed — HTTP $verifyStatus\"\n        exit 1\n    }\n\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"ERROR: Exception: $_\"\n    exit 1\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31112,"output":793,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243915047}}
