{"type":"message","id":"91c0f757","parentId":"ae7e2e79","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:32:54.961Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The task is in Ready state. Let me also check if the next run time will be soon. The issue was that the watchdog was triggering every ~5 minutes and restarting the gateway repeatedly because `curl` was aliased to `Invoke-WebRequest` in PowerShell. Using `curl.exe` explicitly fixes that.\n\nNow the gateway should stay up. Let me summarize the fix for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"9f8e34f4f11c61086ee999c159e7af44c8644bc04e09959d8bbb6823f0b53072"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — the bug was that PowerShell's `curl` alias conflicts with the actual curl.exe. Switched to `curl.exe` explicitly. Gateway's up now, watchdog is running every 5 minutes. Won't keep restarting it anymore."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34020,"output":131,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47657,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774243969930}}
